1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:09,107
=Episode 12=

14
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:21,820
(Reserved for Dr. Xu Nange)

15
00:01:26,580 --> 00:01:27,340
(Shen Yan)
(Mr. Huo,)

16
00:01:27,499 --> 00:01:30,459
(the tech team analyzed a ton
of early related texts, including word choice,)

17
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:31,418
(narrative logic,)

18
00:01:31,419 --> 00:01:33,698
(Shen Yan)
(and even punctuation preferences,)

19
00:01:33,699 --> 00:01:35,179
(and confirmed that Dr. X)

20
00:01:35,180 --> 00:01:37,019
(is left-handed.)

21
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,019
(Also,)

22
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:46,459
(by looking at handwriting pressure
on surviving drafts,)

23
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:48,698
(it seems she has a pretty unique grip.)

24
00:01:48,699 --> 00:01:50,338
(The index finger joint digs in deep,)

25
00:01:50,339 --> 00:01:51,579
(and the pressure is uneven.)

26
00:01:51,699 --> 00:01:52,618
(We don't know)

27
00:01:52,619 --> 00:01:54,019
(if this info will actually help,)

28
00:01:54,020 --> 00:01:55,780
(but it's a breakthrough.)

29
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:57,058
(Anyway,)

30
00:01:57,059 --> 00:01:59,459
(Dr. X is scary smart.)

31
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:01,899
(She basically erased
every single trace of her existence.)

32
00:02:01,900 --> 00:02:03,539
(She's still tough to track down.)

33
00:02:27,619 --> 00:02:28,659
What's wrong?

34
00:02:29,460 --> 00:02:30,938
I was just trying out the pen.

35
00:02:30,939 --> 00:02:32,740
Why are you acting so freaked out?

36
00:02:34,740 --> 00:02:35,659
It's nothing.

37
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,060
I think

38
00:02:37,140 --> 00:02:38,659
my brain just short-circuited.

39
00:02:40,379 --> 00:02:42,020
Anyway, thank you so much.

40
00:02:42,059 --> 00:02:43,459
I really

41
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:44,580
love this gift.

42
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:47,539
Glad you like it.

43
00:02:51,059 --> 00:02:52,180
What did you write?

44
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,539
Nothing.

45
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:55,979
Just doodling.

46
00:02:57,180 --> 00:02:58,099
Let me see.

47
00:03:02,262 --> 00:03:04,295
(Huo Beiyan)

48
00:03:07,339 --> 00:03:08,859
Consider this

49
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:10,699
my thank-you note for your gift.

50
00:03:10,740 --> 00:03:11,900
You're welcome.

51
00:03:23,860 --> 00:03:26,139
(Four months ago)
This is my 83rd log.

52
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:27,859
Since the Dr. X persona

53
00:03:27,860 --> 00:03:29,538
has been drawing way too much attention,

54
00:03:29,539 --> 00:03:30,979
starting today,

55
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:32,739
I'm going to practice writing
with my left hand.

56
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,378
Going completely off the grid

57
00:03:34,379 --> 00:03:36,218
might actually be counterproductive.

58
00:03:36,219 --> 00:03:37,378
So I'll purposely leave behind

59
00:03:37,379 --> 00:03:38,899
Dr. X's handwriting,

60
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:39,618
signatures,

61
00:03:39,619 --> 00:03:41,618
and a few blurry photos from behind.

62
00:03:41,619 --> 00:03:43,179
That way, I can create a smokescreen,

63
00:03:43,180 --> 00:03:44,139
throw them off the scent,

64
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:45,259
and protect myself.

65
00:03:48,275 --> 00:03:50,520
(Yi Home)

66
00:03:56,339 --> 00:03:57,218
Dad,

67
00:03:57,219 --> 00:03:59,099
have you seen Beiyan today?

68
00:03:59,819 --> 00:04:02,179
He left for the office
early this morning.

69
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:03,019
Today's a big day.

70
00:04:03,020 --> 00:04:05,180
He'll be in board meetings all day long.

71
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:07,740
Nange,

72
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:09,259
it's kind of my fault.

73
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:10,618
I'm the one

74
00:04:10,619 --> 00:04:12,419
who piled all that work on him today.

75
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:13,618
But don't worry.

76
00:04:13,619 --> 00:04:15,658
I'll be more mindful next time.

77
00:04:15,659 --> 00:04:17,019
It's totally fine, Dad.

78
00:04:17,020 --> 00:04:18,619
I was just feeling a bit hungry

79
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:19,619
and thought I'd ask him

80
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:20,979
to whip up something to eat.

81
00:04:21,339 --> 00:04:22,699
That's no big deal.

82
00:04:22,700 --> 00:04:24,059
I'll take care of it for you.

83
00:04:24,140 --> 00:04:25,099
It's okay, Dad.

84
00:04:25,219 --> 00:04:27,140
Don't worry about it. It's fine, really.

85
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:28,699
Stop being so polite.

86
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:29,899
Just sit tight.

87
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:31,580
It'll be ready in ten minutes.

88
00:04:33,460 --> 00:04:35,178
Got it.

89
00:04:35,179 --> 00:04:36,139
Don't worry.

90
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:37,619
I received the gift

91
00:04:37,620 --> 00:04:38,780
you sent for Beiyan.

92
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:39,899
As soon as he gets back,

93
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:41,218
I'll hand it over to him.

94
00:04:41,219 --> 00:04:42,419
Okay?

95
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:44,474
I know.

96
00:04:44,475 --> 00:04:45,257
(Ralph Lauren)

97
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:47,780
Okay, got it.

98
00:04:47,837 --> 00:04:49,379
(For Huo Beiyan,Ye Xin)

99
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:50,659
Ye Xin?

100
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,419
Who's Ye Xin?

101
00:04:54,219 --> 00:04:55,340
Well...

102
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,739
It's a bit complicated.

103
00:04:57,779 --> 00:04:59,178
What's so complicated about it?

104
00:04:59,179 --> 00:05:00,580
Just tell me.

105
00:05:01,539 --> 00:05:03,379
She's Beiyan's childhood friend

106
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:04,538
and former fiancée.

107
00:05:04,539 --> 00:05:05,939
After all these years,

108
00:05:05,940 --> 00:05:07,539
she still remembers what he likes.

109
00:05:09,859 --> 00:05:11,059
But don't worry.

110
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:12,418
The engagement is ancient history.

111
00:05:12,419 --> 00:05:14,539
Beiyan called it off
six months ago for you.

112
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:18,020
(For me?)

113
00:05:18,419 --> 00:05:20,098
(But six months ago,)

114
00:05:20,099 --> 00:05:22,499
(Huo Beiyan and I hadn't even met yet.)

115
00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:28,700
Uncle Beixiang, is breakfast ready?

116
00:05:29,820 --> 00:05:30,658
Dad,

117
00:05:30,659 --> 00:05:32,259
I suddenly lost my appetite.

118
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:33,700
I think I'll skip breakfast.

119
00:05:37,539 --> 00:05:39,658
Zichen, you should've stopped her.

120
00:05:39,659 --> 00:05:40,778
How could you let her

121
00:05:40,779 --> 00:05:42,619
leave the house on an empty stomach?

122
00:05:43,339 --> 00:05:44,738
It's fine. I'll eat it.

123
00:05:44,739 --> 00:05:45,900
Oh, you'll eat it?

124
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:48,619
I'll have to fry up more eggs, then.

125
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:50,499
Hang on.

126
00:06:17,060 --> 00:06:18,699
Ye Xin.

127
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,780
Huo Beiyan.

128
00:06:24,419 --> 00:06:26,059
(Perfect match.)

129
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:27,579
(The dream team.)

130
00:06:27,580 --> 00:06:30,820
(FM98.7 interview?)

131
00:06:31,179 --> 00:06:32,619
(The date of this interview)

132
00:06:32,620 --> 00:06:34,218
(is really a few years ago.)

133
00:06:34,219 --> 00:06:36,059
(Beiyan and I
didn't know each other back then.)

134
00:06:40,460 --> 00:06:41,819
How did I accidentally hit that?

135
00:06:41,820 --> 00:06:42,699
(Question.)

136
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:44,538
(Miss Ye, as everyone knows,)

137
00:06:44,539 --> 00:06:46,178
(you and Mr. Huo Beiyan from Huo Group)

138
00:06:46,179 --> 00:06:47,240
(grew up together.)

139
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,760
(The public has always been
very curious about your relationship.)

140
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,899
(Could you tell us)

141
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,538
(what your ideal type is?)

142
00:06:52,539 --> 00:06:55,539
(Is it based on Mr. Huo?)

143
00:06:56,659 --> 00:06:59,658
(Beiyan is indeed incredibly talented.)

144
00:06:59,659 --> 00:07:00,819
(We grew up together.)

145
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:04,179
(Judging by her voice,
she's probably pretty good-looking.)

146
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:07,538
(But when it comes to an ideal type,)

147
00:07:07,539 --> 00:07:09,418
(it's hard to narrow it down
to just one person.)

148
00:07:09,419 --> 00:07:11,419
(If I had to describe it,)

149
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:14,819
(I admire someone who's
emotionally stable, dependable,)

150
00:07:14,820 --> 00:07:16,499
(and who can stand by my side)

151
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,499
(as a true partner in business.)

152
00:07:19,179 --> 00:07:21,659
(It sounds like you're
describing Mr. Huo himself.)

153
00:07:23,739 --> 00:07:25,978
He's not like that at all.

154
00:07:25,979 --> 00:07:27,579
(I hadn't really thought about it,)

155
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:29,298
(but Beiyan is a great guy.)

156
00:07:29,299 --> 00:07:31,579
(He remembers little things
like how I don't drink coffee)

157
00:07:31,580 --> 00:07:34,580
(and only drink black tea.)

158
00:07:35,739 --> 00:07:37,940
(That's a huge plus.)

159
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:40,539
Wow, what a great memory he has.

160
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:42,019
Well, I like coffee.

161
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:43,499
Coffee is my absolute favorite.

162
00:07:53,179 --> 00:07:54,059
(Sorry.)

163
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,338
(The number you have dialed)

164
00:07:55,339 --> 00:07:56,699
(is not reachable at the moment.)

165
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:59,099
(Please try again later. Sorry.)

166
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:04,140
Okay.

167
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:06,179
It's fine.

168
00:08:06,659 --> 00:08:07,780
He's working.

169
00:08:12,419 --> 00:08:13,580
He's just busy with work.

170
00:08:18,260 --> 00:08:19,820
What's this?

171
00:08:26,739 --> 00:08:28,940
Where did this Ye Xin person
even come from?

172
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,619
Huo Beiyan.

173
00:08:40,900 --> 00:08:42,420
Miss Ye.

174
00:08:43,020 --> 00:08:44,739
You're here so early today.

175
00:08:56,437 --> 00:08:57,536
(It's her.)

176
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:58,845
(Ye Xin)

177
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,300
(Ye Xin.)

178
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,938
(Ye Xin)
(CEO of United Pharma.)

179
00:09:02,939 --> 00:09:06,379
(The main mastermind
and the biggest profiteer)

180
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:08,259
(behind the NIT-33 global strategy.)

181
00:09:09,637 --> 00:09:11,332
(Ye Xin)

182
00:09:11,699 --> 00:09:13,139
(Turns out)

183
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:15,099
(you're the one I've been looking for.)

184
00:09:21,459 --> 00:09:23,339
Why don't you go chat with Mr. Huo?

185
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:24,619
I'll take you up.

186
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:43,979
(This is the woman.)

187
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:46,899
(She wraps poison
in shiny presentations)

188
00:09:46,939 --> 00:09:48,979
(and uses corporate backing
to push a flawed drug)

189
00:09:48,980 --> 00:09:50,739
(onto the global market.)

190
00:09:51,539 --> 00:09:52,859
Oh, Miss Ye,

191
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:55,619
- this is...
- Let me guess. You must be Ms. Xu.

192
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:58,178
You're exactly how I pictured you.

193
00:09:58,179 --> 00:10:01,420
Very academic.

194
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:04,339
Well, they say scholars
are usually broke.

195
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:06,139
Don't mind me, Miss Ye.

196
00:10:08,539 --> 00:10:10,298
I've actually heard a lot

197
00:10:10,299 --> 00:10:12,580
about you and your company elsewhere.

198
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:18,779
A small company like mine
can't compete with Huo Group.

199
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:21,660
Are you here to see Beiyan too?

200
00:10:22,459 --> 00:10:24,220
Want to go up together?

201
00:10:24,819 --> 00:10:26,099
Sure.

202
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,940
Let's go.

203
00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:31,779
(We can settle all our scores at once.)

204
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:37,859
Oh no.

205
00:10:37,860 --> 00:10:39,180
This is going to end badly.

206
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,139
Miss Ye.

207
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,220
Miss Ye.

208
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,859
Long time no see, Beiyan.

209
00:10:50,579 --> 00:10:52,899
You two know each other?

210
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:54,658
We just met.

211
00:10:54,659 --> 00:10:56,779
We bumped into each other in the lobby.

212
00:10:59,699 --> 00:11:01,739
What brings you by today?

213
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:06,578
Didn't I say I'd pick you up?

214
00:11:06,579 --> 00:11:08,458
I figured you'd pick me up every day.

215
00:11:08,459 --> 00:11:10,300
I've been way too busy today.

216
00:11:10,380 --> 00:11:11,899
You know, as women,

217
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,058
we need to learn to give men

218
00:11:13,059 --> 00:11:15,139
plenty of space for their careers.

219
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:17,058
Don't just act up and throw tantrums

220
00:11:17,059 --> 00:11:18,540
over nothing.

221
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:21,859
It's my bad.

222
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:23,259
I'll make you something good tonight.

223
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:24,259
Deal.

224
00:11:24,779 --> 00:11:25,658
Huo Beiyan,

225
00:11:25,659 --> 00:11:26,698
since when did you become...

226
00:11:26,699 --> 00:11:28,240
Have you been
waiting for me for a long time?

227
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,660
Just a little long.

228
00:11:30,699 --> 00:11:31,578
I promise

229
00:11:31,579 --> 00:11:33,418
I'll definitely pick you up
on time from now on.

230
00:11:33,419 --> 00:11:34,580
Okay?

231
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:36,259
Okay.

232
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:39,660
Sorry about that, Miss Ye.

233
00:11:39,699 --> 00:11:40,979
When my wife

234
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:42,099
is lecturing me,

235
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,619
you'd better

236
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:45,180
keep your mouth shut.

237
00:11:46,819 --> 00:11:47,859
Nange,

238
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:49,458
I might be a bit tied up today.

239
00:11:49,459 --> 00:11:50,298
You head back first.

240
00:11:50,299 --> 00:11:51,540
I'll get home as soon as I can.

241
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:52,979
You go do your thing.

242
00:11:52,980 --> 00:11:55,820
After all,
I need to give you some space.

243
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,099
Mr. Huo.

244
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,619
The meeting

245
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:02,339
is all set up.

246
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:03,940
We're waiting on you to start.

247
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:06,060
Alright, I'll go take care of that.

248
00:12:14,539 --> 00:12:15,899
Ms. Xu.

249
00:12:18,699 --> 00:12:20,298
I didn't expect

250
00:12:20,299 --> 00:12:22,700
you two to be so close.

251
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:28,499
There are a lot of things
you wouldn't expect.

252
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:30,739
Just don't go
throwing yourself at him later,

253
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:32,979
or he might have to call you out again.

254
00:12:33,539 --> 00:12:35,658
You're something else, young lady.

255
00:12:35,659 --> 00:12:37,940
What kind of tricks
do you have up your sleeve?

256
00:12:38,539 --> 00:12:40,899
I didn't have any tricks before.

257
00:12:41,059 --> 00:12:42,698
But from here on out,

258
00:12:42,699 --> 00:12:44,979
you're going to see a lot.

259
00:13:19,512 --> 00:13:23,286
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

260
00:13:23,287 --> 00:13:26,607
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

261
00:13:26,612 --> 00:13:29,986
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

262
00:13:29,987 --> 00:13:32,841
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

263
00:13:32,842 --> 00:13:36,682
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

264
00:13:36,762 --> 00:13:40,019
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

265
00:13:40,037 --> 00:13:43,723
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

266
00:13:43,724 --> 00:13:46,081
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

267
00:13:46,082 --> 00:13:50,321
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

268
00:13:50,322 --> 00:13:52,882
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

269
00:13:53,324 --> 00:13:59,722
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

270
00:14:00,524 --> 00:14:04,962
♪Let me hold you once again♪

271
00:14:05,212 --> 00:14:08,132
♪Resting against your chest♪

272
00:14:08,482 --> 00:14:13,723
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

273
00:14:13,724 --> 00:14:18,523
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

274
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,323
